// MongoDB Start From Here

Model the following University information system as a graph model, and
answer the following queries using Cypher.
University has various departments like Physics, Geography, Computer etc.
Each department conducts various courses and a course may be conducted by
multiple departments. Every course may have recommendations provided by
people.

Identify the labels and relationships, along with their properties, anddraw
a high-level Graph model.

Create nodes and relationships, along with their properties, and
visualize your actual Graph model.
CREATE
(d1:Department {name:'Physics'}),
(d2:Department {name:'Geography'}),
(d3:Department {name:'Computer'}),
(d4:Department {name:'Mathematics'}),

(c1:Course {name:'Quantum Mechanics', code:'PHY101'}),
(c2:Course {name:'Astrophysics', code:'PHY102'}),
(c3:Course {name:'Geography Basics', code:'GEO101'}),
(c4:Course {name:'Data Structures', code:'CS101'}),
(c5:Course {name:'Algorithms', code:'CS102'}),
(c6:Course {name:'Calculus', code:'MATH101'}),
(c7:Course {name:'Linear Algebra', code:'MATH102'}),
(c8:Course {name:'Computer Graphics', code:'CS103'}),

(p1:Person {name:'Rahul'}),
(p2:Person {name:'Sita'}),
(p3:Person {name:'Amresh'}),

(d1)-[:OFFERS]->(c1),
(d1)-[:OFFERS]->(c2),
(d2)-[:OFFERS]->(c3),
(d3)-[:OFFERS]->(c4),
(d3)-[:OFFERS]->(c5),
(d3)-[:OFFERS]->(c8),
(d4)-[:OFFERS]->(c6),
(d4)-[:OFFERS]->(c7),
(d3)-[:OFFERS]->(c7), // Linear Algebra offered by both CS and Math

(c1)-[:RECOMMENDED_BY]->(p1),
(c3)-[:RECOMMENDED_BY]->(p2),
(c4)-[:RECOMMENDED_BY]->(p3),
(c7)-[:RECOMMENDED_BY]->(p1),
(c7)-[:RECOMMENDED_BY]->(p2);

Answer the following Queries :
a. List the details of all the departments in the university.
MATCH (d:Department)
RETURN d.name;

b. List the names of the courses provided by Physics department.
MATCH (d:Department {name:'Physics'})-[:OFFERS]->(c:Course)
RETURN c.name, c.code;

c. List the most recommended course in Geography department.
MATCH (d:Department {name:'Geography'})-[:OFFERS]->(c:Course)
OPTIONAL MATCH (c)-[:RECOMMENDED_BY]->(p:Person)
RETURN c.name, count(p) AS Recommendations
ORDER BY Recommendations DESC
LIMIT 1;

d. List the names of common courses across Mathematics and computer department.
MATCH (d1:Department {name:'Mathematics'})-[:OFFERS]->(c:Course)<-[:OFFERS]-(d2:Department {name:'Computer'})
RETURN c.name, c.code